com.foreach.across.modules.filemanager.services

Class CachedFileResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.filemanager.services.CachedFileResource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FileRepositoryResource, FileResource, ExpiringFileResource, org.springframework.core.io.InputStreamSource, org.springframework.core.io.Resource, org.springframework.core.io.WritableResource

    public class CachedFileResource
extends Object
implements ExpiringFileResource
    Represents a caching wrapper around a target FileResource. Takes two file resources as parameter. One is the actual target, the other contains the cached data. If the latter exists it will be used instead of the target for access.

    Note that the Resource.exists() will be called often on the cache resource, it can be any type of file resource, but you usually want it to come from a LocalFileRepository.

    The cache is primarily used for the actual data streams, other methods might forward directly to the target resource to ensure maximum consistency.

    Since:
    1.4.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
